# ============================================================
# MARKET CORE RUNTIME
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: runtime
domain: market
scope: market.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines core runtime handling for market.

## runtime_scope
Runtime covers listing visibility,
search/browse exposure,
state-aware display,
bounded participation actions,
and safe failure rendering.

## current_view_state
Runtime-visible market state must distinguish:
- currently visible listings
- restricted listings
- hidden listings
- historical listings
- closed listings

## transition_rules
Runtime transitions move through:
entry,
identity resolution,
listing-state resolution,
validation,
visibility/render execution,
and bounded failure handling.

## projection_rules
Runtime may present rankings,
sorting,
or highlighted exposure,
but these must not overwrite source truth.

## masking_rules
Masked listings and masked market outputs
must remain identifiable as masked.

## validation_rules
- source identity must resolve
- listing authority must resolve
- market state must resolve
- viewer scope must be valid
- policy scope must be valid

## failure_modes
- invalid listing identity
- invalid visibility state
- invalid viewer scope
- policy conflict
- safe render fallback

## observability
Runtime must emit enough signals
to distinguish listing state,
source relation,
validation result,
visibility result,
and failure surface.

## review_checklist
- visibility states are explicit
- projection limits are explicit
- validation gating is explicit
- failure handling is explicit
